{"word":"καταράομαι","slug":"καταράομαι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>καταράομαι</b></el> <el>(ionic <el>-αρεόμαι</el>) (<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>άσομαι</el>) (ionic <el>ήσομαι</el>) </el><p/><a href='S:Deponent Verb, i.e. a Verb of Middle or Passive form with Active sense'>Dep.</a><p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to call down curses upon, imprecate upon</i>, <el>τί τινι</el> <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>:—<a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a>, <el>καταρῶνται ἀπολέσθαι</el> <i>they pray</i> that he may perish, <b><a href='S:Theognis'>Theogn.</a></b>:—<a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a> <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a> only, <i>to curse, execrate</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; later, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a>, <b><a href='S:Plutarch'>Plut.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:New Testament'>NTest.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a> <i>to utter imprecations</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><a href='S:perfect tense'>perf.</a> <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a> <a href='S:participle'>part.</a> <el>κατ-ηρᾱμένος</el> in <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a> sense, <i>accursed</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}